            "answer_text": "The most serious limitation depends on the application you\u2019re trying to use it for. But overall, a big one is sensitivity: the NMR signal derives from differences in the population of nuclear spin states. Since the two eigenstates of nuclear spin are relatively close in energy even in a strong magnetic field, this population difference is low, and the signal strength of NMR relative to other techniques (like optical spectroscopy) is therefore low. (I can give a better answer to a more specific question, if you update it.) ",
